[div class=p 
	[em 
		"Fantasy Zone
	]em
	" is a shoot 'em up game that was initially developed by Sega as an arcade game and is the first game in the 
	[em 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Fantasy Zone|href=/GameGroups/50)
	]em
	" series. It later received ports for home systems such as the NES, Sega Master System, and PC Engine. The game is best known for its cute aesthetic that it popularized for shoot 'em ups, and for popularizing the boss rush concept, where multiple bosses are fought in succession without breaks.
